The paper deals with the classification of maximum distance separable (MDS) codes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves combinatorial methods (cs.DM) for classifying codes and the use of linear codes (cs.SI) to show equivalence between certain codes. Additionally, the paper discusses error-correcting codes (cs.NI) and their properties.
